comments.body:
@eparis nothing in this prevents a maintainer from hitting the green button to merge a qualified PR.

However it _does_ require that the PR be approved by an OWNER.  This could be the author of the PR, if they are an OWNER for that area, or they will need to find someone.  That's explicitly the point of this PR.  I don't think committers should be able to commit code without OWNER approval.

(and obviously we will have some top-level OWNERS for emergencies)
